    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "Imam al-Sadiq enumerates the ten noble character traits (makarim al-akhlaq) that God bestowed upon Prophet Muhammad: certainty, contentment, patience, gratitude, forbearance, good character, generosity, protectiveness, courage, and chivalry. He urges believers to examine themselves for these traits and to ask God for increase in them. This hadith, reported in the assembly of al-Saduq, provided a practical moral checklist for the early Shia community.",
        "key_terms": {
          "مكارم الأخلاق": "Makarim al-Akhlaq - noble character traits, the highest moral virtues",
          "اليقين": "Al-Yaqin - certainty, firm faith without doubt",
          "المروءة": "Al-Muru'ah - chivalry, manly virtue encompassing dignity and honor"
        },
        "seo_question": "What are the ten noble character traits of Prophet Muhammad?"
      },
      "ur": {
        "summary": "امام صادق علیہ السلام نے رسول اکرم کی دس مکارم اخلاق بیان فرمائیں اور مؤمنین کو ان کی جانچ اور اضافے کی ترغیب دی۔",
        "key_terms": {
          "مكارم الأخلاق": "مکارم اخلاق - بلند اخلاقی صفات",
          "اليقين": "یقین - قطعی ایمان",
          "المروءة": "مروت - جوانمردی"
        },
        "seo_question": "نبی اکرم کی دس مکارم اخلاق کیا ہیں؟"
